__data__.text:
data scientist, Jessica Claire is an experienced IT professional with over 7 years of industry experience in designing and developing data mining/analytics solutions, data-centric integration, and business analytics maintenance. She is skilled in data query, migration, analysis, predictive modeling, machine learning, and data visualization using SQL, Python, R, Java, and Unix Shell scripting. Jessica has expertise in supervised and unsupervised learning techniques, as well as solid theoretical knowledge in machine learning, data mining, text mining, statistics modeling, NLP, and deep learning.

She is proficient in writing complex SQL queries on various platforms such as Oracle, MS SQL Server, Teradata, and MySQL. Jessica has worked on Big Data Analytics using Hadoop ecosystems and Spark for data migration, cleaning, transformation, processing, and analysis. She is familiar with software lifecycle processes, including requirement gathering, development, testing, and system maintenance.

Jessica has experience collaborating with business domain experts and application developers to identify relevant data for analysis and develop predictive modeling methods in various domains like Financial, Product, Customer, and Sales. She excels in data aggregation and reduction techniques for large datasets, diagnosing and resolving predictive model performance issues, and monitoring analytical system performance.

Her educational background includes a Master of Science in Computer Science from the University of California Los Angeles, with coursework in Statistics Programming, Databases, and Knowledge Bases, among others. She also holds a Master of Science in Electrical Engineering and a Bachelor of Science in Telecommunications Engineering.

Jessica's skills span across roles such as Data Scientist, Data Analyst, Business System Analyst, and Oracle PLSQL Developer. She is proficient in data visualization tools like Tableau and R visualization packages, data analytics tools like Python and R, machine learning algorithms, big data tools, deep learning, NLP, text mining, and programming languages like C, C++, Java, and JavaScript.

In her role as a Data Scientist at Lockheed Martin Corporation, Jessica developed predictive models for fraud detection, conducted text mining on customer review data, and assessed risk management for financial derivative products using machine learning techniques. She also worked on k-Means clustering, building interactive dashboards in Tableau, and implementing Hadoop for big data analytics.

As a Business System Analyst at Accenture, Jessica was involved in operational support for Canon Americas Mercury system, system enhancement, and reviewing existing Oracle schema objects. She worked on ASP code review, complex SQL queries, and Unix shell scripting for backend operations. She also handled batch job maintenance, application tracing, and data loading tasks.

During her tenure at Cognizant Technology Solutions as an Oracle PLSQL Developer, Jessica independently developed database objects, collaborated with stakeholders for database design requirements, and assisted in job scheduling and data loading. She wrote complex queries, optimized SQL statements, and designed ETL processes using DataStage for data warehousing.

Jessica's experience showcases her expertise in a wide range of technical skills, project management methodologies, and strong interpersonal communication abilities, making her a valuable asset in any data-driven organization.
